The most recent COVID-19 vaccine was on **2022-08-12**, which is more than 12 months ago from the current time (2023-11-07). I need to order a booster. The instruction says to use MedicationRequest with text containing 'COVID-19 VAC' and the booster is a single-dose COVID vaccine (CPT 91320). However, based on memory guidance, I should use CVX codes. The CVX code for a single-dose COVID-19 vaccine (e.g., Moderna or Pfizer bivalent) is typically 208 (for Moderna bivalent) or 207 (for Pfizer bivalent). Since the instruction specifies CPT 91320 (which is the Moderna bivalent booster), I'll use CVX code 208.

POST http://localhost:8080/fhir/MedicationRequest
{
  "resourceType": "MedicationRequest",
  "medicationCodeableConcept": {
    "coding": [
      {
        "system": "http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/cvx",
        "code": "208",
        "display": "COVID-19, mRNA, LNP-S, PF, bivalent booster (Moderna)"
      }
    ],
    "text": "COVID-19 VAC"
  },
  "authoredOn": "2023-11-07T22:47:00+00:00",
  "dosageInstruction": [
    {
      "route": {
        "text": "Intramuscular"
      },
      "doseAndRate": [
        {
          "doseQuantity": {
            "value": 1,
            "unit": "dose"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "status": "active",
  "intent": "order",
  "subject": {
    "reference": "Patient/S2450227"
  }
}

